=== Acquisition process ===

The Authority intends to procure a first batch of six trainsets for deployment on the Initial Operating Segment (IOS) as well as a "driving simulator". Included will be services for maintenance for 30&nbsp;years, a mid-life overhaul, and a variety of support services.
In January 2024, the Authority chose [[Alstom]] and [[Siemens Mobility]] as qualified train suppliers.<ref>{{cite web |title="NEWS RELEASE: High-Speed Rail Authority Releases Shortlist of Potential Suppliers for Electrified High-Speed Trains in California" |date=January 6, 2024 |url=https://hsr.ca.gov/2024/01/05/news-release-high-speed-rail-authority-releases-shortlist-of-potential-suppliers-for-electrified-high-speed-trains-in-california/ |publisher=CAHSR Authority |access-date=January 6, 2024 |archive-date=January 6, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240106025701/https://hsr.ca.gov/2024/01/05/news-release-high-speed-rail-authority-releases-shortlist-of-potential-suppliers-for-electrified-high-speed-trains-in-california/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

The Authority released a ''request for proposals'' (RFP) in mid-April 2024, with a procurement contract planned for summer 2025.<ref>{{cite news |last1=May |first1=Tiana |title=California High-Speed Rail Releases RFP for Electric Train Contract |url=https://railway-news.com/california-high-speed-rail-releases-rfp-for-electric-train-contract/ |access-date=September 2, 2024 |work=Railway News |date=April 17, 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://hsr.ca.gov/business-opportunities/procurements/architectural-engineering-and-capital-contracts/high-speed-trainsets-and-related-services/ |access-date=2025-01-25 |website=[[California High-Speed Rail Authority]]|title=High-Speed Trainsets and Related Services}}</ref> The chosen contractor will have to deliver two prototype trainsets for testing by the end of 2028 and four further trainsets by 2030 for revenue service on the IOS.<ref name="board memo trainset rfq">{{cite web |title=CHSRA Board Meeting Briefing: Trainset RFQ |url=https://hsr.ca.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/August-4-2023-Agenda-Item-2-Board-Memo-Trainsets-RFQ-Final-A11Y.pdf |publisher=[[California High-Speed Rail Authority]] |access-date=March 10, 2024 |archive-date=March 10, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240310192514/https://hsr.ca.gov/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/August-4-2023-Agenda-Item-2-Board-Memo-Trainsets-RFQ-Final-A11Y.pdf |url-status=live }}</ref> There is also an option for a further 15&nbsp;trainsets. In 2023, it was projected that for the full Phase&nbsp;1 system, 66&nbsp;trainsets would be needed.<ref name="2023 Project Update Report"/>

Because the trainset purchase is funded by an FRA grant program authorized under the [[Infrastructure Investment and Jobs Act]], manufacturing and sourcing for the trainsets fall under provisions of the [[Buy America Act]]. Both qualified bidders have local manufacturing capacities: Alstom in [[Hornell, New York#Hornell in the post-railroad period (1960–present)|Hornell, New York]] and Siemens Mobility in [[Horseheads (village), New York|Horseheads, New York]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-09 |title=Siemens Mobility to establish America's first high-speed rail production facility in Horseheads, New York |url=https://www.mobility.siemens.com/us/en/company/newsroom/press-releases/siemens-mobility-to-establish-americas-first-high-speed-rail-production-facility-in-horseheads-new-york.html |access-date=2024-09-09 |website=Siemens Mobility Global |language=en}}</ref> The Authority was granted a Buy America-waiver by the [[Federal Railroad Administration|FRA]] for the two prototype trainsets, allowing those to be manufactured abroad.<ref name="fra chsra waiver">{{cite web |title=California High Speed Rail Authority Prototypes Buy America Waiver Decision |url=https://railroads.dot.gov/elibrary/california-high-speed-rail-authority-prototypes-buy-america-waiver-decision |publisher=Federal Railroad Administration |access-date=March 10, 2024 |archive-date=March 19, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240319222836/https://railroads.dot.gov/elibrary/california-high-speed-rail-authority-prototypes-buy-america-waiver-decision |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Stations and service ==

